flavor_text_entries.ruby:
BARBOACH’s sensitive whiskers serve
as a superb radar system.
This POKéMON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits
for prey to come along.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
BARBOACH’s body is covered with a
slimy film. If a foe grabs it, this
POKéMON just slips out of the enemy’s grip.
This POKéMON grows weak if the slimy
coating dries up.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
Its body is covered with a slimy film.
The film acts as a barrier to prevent germs
in muddy water from entering the
BARBOACH’s body.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
It probes muddy riverbeds with its two
long whiskers. A slimy film protects its
body.
flavor_text_entries.leafgreen:
It probes muddy riverbeds with its two
long whiskers. A slimy film protects its
body.
flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It coats its entire body with a
slimy fluid so it can squirm and
slip away if grabbed.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
Its whiskers make a superb radar.
They are used to locate prey,
even in the murkiest of water.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In
one region, it is said to have been
born from hardened mud.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
BARBOACH uses its whiskers to
taste things just as a person uses
his or her tongue to taste things.

flavor_text_entries.omega-ruby:

This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers

flavor_text_entries.alpha-sapphire:
Barboach’s body is covered with a slimy film. If a foe grabs it,
this Pokémon just slips out of the enemy’s grip. This Pokémon
grows weak if the slimy coating dries up.
flavor_text_entries.sun:
Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar.
Even in muddy waters, it can detect its
prey’s location.
flavor_text_entries.moon:
Its slippery body is hard to grasp, so much so
that there are festivals where people compete
to see how many they can catch barehanded.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
Its entire body is gooey. When pecked at by
bird Pokémon, it slips and slides its way
to freedom.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
Its whiskers are filled with nerves. They can
sense smells and flavors just as a person’s nose
or tongue would.

flavor_text_entries.shield:

flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
Makes its home in swamps with murky water. The poor visibility
hides this Pokémon from predators, and the slime on its body
makes grasping it difficult.
